00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:25,890
Yes, as a joke, Chief

271
00:24:25,890 --> 00:24:30,190
has occasionally told stories about the knight seducing the princess to take over the castle.

272
00:24:30,190 --> 00:24:32,300
But that knight

273
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:36,270
really fell in love with the princess, so he was agonizing over it.

274
00:24:36,270 --> 00:24:38,260
Would he be able to take over the castle like that?

275
00:24:38,260 --> 00:24:42,040
Exactly. On top of that,  he said that this princess met another knight and confessed to him.

276
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:45,720
But after seeing her getting rejected and crying, he said his heart was really in pain.

277
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:49,810
That's not it. At first I also thought that it might be Chief's story, but it's not.

278
00:24:49,810 --> 00:24:53,240
You two are always close and decisively, you

279
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:56,780
wouldn't confess to another knight or anything.

280
00:24:56,780 --> 00:24:59,620
 I'll tell you my heart clearly so listen carefully.

281
00:24:59,620 --> 00:25:04,230
 No matter what I do in the future, forgive me.

282
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:08,340
Um, perhaps did the chief

283
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,530
say why that knight tried to take over the castle?

284
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:14,500
I don't think so. He didn't talk about that.

285
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:30,960

286
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:37,410
 The person is not available, so after the beep...

287
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:40,120
Doctor Park.

288
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:48,660
What are you saying? That Chief Han is planning something?

289
00:25:48,660 --> 00:25:51,040
I'm asking just in case.

290
00:25:51,790 --> 00:25:56,300
He's a person who wants to finish the Prime Minister's surgery well so he can become the boss of your hospital.

291
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:59,030
But he said something strange to me.

292
00:25:59,030 --> 00:26:00,820
What do you mean by something strange.

293
00:26:00,820 --> 00:26:04,510
He said that no matter what he does, he asked me to forgive him.

294
00:26:04,510 --> 00:26:06,240
No matter what he does?

295
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:09,850
Yes, it's making me nervous.

296
00:26:11,650 --> 00:26:13,480
 About going to North Korea.

297
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:17,440
 Actually, I don't think I ever told you about that.

298
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,610
 Among my friends I met at Harvard,

299
00:26:20,610 --> 00:26:24,020
 I had a friend named Lee Seung Hoon.

300
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,740
Why?

301
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:33,620
He's not really planning something scary, right?

302
00:26:33,620 --> 00:26:36,390
By any chance, do you know someone named Lee Seung Hoon among Chief Han's friends?

303
00:26:36,390 --> 00:26:38,780
I don't. Who is that?

304
00:26:38,780 --> 00:26:41,590
He is the son of the victim of a medical malpractice lawsuit from 20 years ago.

305
00:26:41,590 --> 00:26:45,310
The thing I told you about before, that lawsuit that sent us to North Korea.

306
00:26:45,990 --> 00:26:48,650
Then could Jae Joon be...

307
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:56,840
That can't be it, right?

308
00:27:09,330 --> 00:27:11,690
Watch over me, Father.

309
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:16,980
The first part of my revenge will start tomorrow.

310
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:51,700
Is Water Bottle not coming?

311
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:53,460
I don't know. How would I know?

312
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:54,780
He was on the same side as you.

313
00:27:54,780 --> 00:27:56,650
Don't you know?

314
00:27:56,650 --> 00:28:02,000
In this world, there's no such thing as a forever comrade or forever enemy.

315
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:05,650
Chairman!

316
00:28:10,700 --> 00:28:12,800
That weed.

317
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,490
Well, we are gathered today,

318
00:28:24,490 --> 00:28:28,770
to  celebrate that our Myeongwoo was chosen as the Prime Minister's surgery team.

319
00:28:28,770 --> 00:28:33,340
Next, the Chief of the Cardiothoracic Department, Han Jae Joon, who has been selected

320
00:28:33,340 --> 00:28:37,830
as the performing surgeon for the Prime Minister's surgery will  come up and say his greetings.

321
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:53,000
More than that, I would like to sincerely thank the Chairman for today.

322
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:56,870
And I'd like to use this opportunity to also thank many doctors who have put in hard work to be chosen as

323
00:28:56,870 --> 00:29:00,060
the Prime Minister's surgery team.

324
00:29:01,060 --> 00:29:04,990
As it's been a long time since we've been out of the hospital,

325
00:29:04,990 --> 00:29:08,670
I wish everyone will have a good time.  Thank you.

326
00:29:13,830 --> 00:29:18,660
After the meal, the Chairman of Myeongwoo University Hospital is due to make an important announcement,

327
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:21,980
so please stay until the end.

328
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:30,360
Hello, Chairman, it's good to see you.

329
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:32,020
- You've been well, right?
- Yes, yes.

330
00:29:32,020 --> 00:29:34,680
You look well as usual.

331
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:37,760
- It's nice to see you looking healthy.
- Thank you.

332
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:39,850
Jae Joon?

333
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:42,920
I have something to ask you.

334
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,780
Don't worry.

335
00:29:44,780 --> 00:29:47,830
It will be a bit difficult to announce our wedding today.

336
00:29:47,830 --> 00:29:50,000
That's not it...

337
00:30:08,980 --> 00:30:11,540
Why did you ask to meet?

338
00:30:11,540 --> 00:30:13,910
I owe you an apology.

339
00:30:14,970 --> 00:30:16,880
Your father's incident...

340
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:19,870
it seems like I had misunderstood.

341
00:30:19,870 --> 00:30:23,010
Did you tell me to come all the way here for just that?

342
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:27,880
I wanted to leave with a good sentiment, at least with you.

343
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:31,370
And there's also a favor I want to ask you.

344
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:35,090
No thank you.  I can't afford the time to listen to your favor.

345
00:30:35,090 --> 00:30:38,730
I'm speaking about Doctor Oh Soo Hyeon.

346
00:30:39,890 --> 00:30:43,970
Soo Hyeon sincerely likes you.

347
00:30:43,970 --> 00:30:47,000
Then were you faking your love for her?

348
00:30:48,390 --> 00:30:51,970
Stop saying nonsense, and don't hurt Quack anymore.

349
00:30:51,970 --> 00:30:55,360
If not, it'll hurt you many times more.

350
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:59,790
I'm telling you not to do anything that you'll regret.  If there's anything you're hiding, then say it before it's too late.

351
00:30:59,790 --> 00:31:03,830
If there's anything you've done wrong, then ask for her forgiveness as soon as possible.

352
00:31:03,830 --> 00:31:06,280
The thing I'm trying to do...

353
00:31:07,130 --> 00:31:10,090
I can't say it to Soo Hyeon,

354
00:31:10,090 --> 00:31:11,830
and I can't be forgiven either.

355
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:13,220
Then just don't do it.

356
00:31:13,220 --> 00:31:15,510
It already started.

357
00:31:29,900 --> 00:31:38,020

358
00:31:44,430 --> 00:31:45,450
What are you doing here?

359
00:31:45,450 --> 00:31:47,290
Oh Sang Jin?

360
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:49,640
Yes, I am.

361
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:53,800
I'm arresting you for embezzlement and bribery.

362
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:59,280
- Father!
- Which district are you guys from?

363
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,430
How dare you come here and abuse your power?

364
00:32:01,430 --> 00:32:03,040
I'll explain the specific details at the station.

365
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:05,590
Which station? Are you guys allowed to arrest people like this?

366
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:07,530
Do you not see this warrant?

367
00:32:07,530 --> 00:32:09,510
- What are you doing?
- Yes.

368
00:32:09,510 --> 00:32:12,250
Father, Father. Father!

369
00:32:12,250 --> 00:32:13,930
Father!

370
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,600
 What is that?  Why?

371
00:32:28,140 --> 00:32:30,830
Did you do this?

372
00:32:30,830 --> 00:32:32,880
It's just the beginning.

373
00:32:33,770 --> 00:32:36,330
The events that will happen from now on as well,

374
00:32:36,330 --> 00:32:38,750
will become scars that will be irrevocable to Soo Hyeon.

375
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,840
Just as I suspected,

376
00:32:41,510 --> 00:32:43,530
you are Lee Seung Hoon.

377
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:48,920
Revenge... are you doing something like that?

378
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:52,100
Wouldn't that be natural if you were Lee Seung Hoon?

379
00:32:52,100 --> 00:32:56,030
After losing my father, I lost my mother, too.

380
00:32:57,530 --> 00:33:00,070
And for 20 years...

381
00:33:00,070 --> 00:33:03,100
I lived with their injustices buried in my heart.

382
00:33:04,530 --> 00:33:07,690
I waited for the opportunity to resolve that deep sorrow,

383
00:33:07,690 --> 00:33:10,310
and since it's finally come,

384
00:33:10,310 --> 00:33:11,610
I have to do it.

385
00:33:11,610 --> 00:33:14,070
He's the father of the woman you love.

386
00:33:14,070 --> 00:33:16,200
She's a woman Han Jae Joon loved.

387
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:19,480
It wasn't Lee Seung Hoon.

388
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:21,490
You're wrong.

389
00:33:22,830 --> 00:33:27,510
Both Han Jae Joon and Lee Seung Hoon loved Oh Soo Hyeon.

390
00:33:27,510 --> 00:33:29,320
Am I wrong?

391
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:42,860
- What happened?
- An anonymous letter was sent to the prosecutors, Chairman.

392
00:33:42,860 --> 00:33:44,390
An anonymous letter?  Who?

393
00:33:44,390 --> 00:33:47,160
Since that was a secret, they couldn't say...

394
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:50,530
but fortunately, there was a hoobae from my hometown among the investigators...

395
00:33:50,530 --> 00:33:52,060
So who was it?

396
00:33:52,060 --> 00:33:55,000
He said it was Lee Seung Hoon.

397
00:33:57,070 --> 00:34:01,030
By chance, have you heard that name before?

398
00:34:02,020 --> 00:34:03,240
Lee Seung Hoon?

399
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:04,610
Yes.

400
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,750
Jae Joon, are you that person?

401
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:31,900
Lee Seung Hoon ... Jae Joon, are you Lee Seung Hoon?

402
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:35,610
- Is that important? 
- Tell me.

403
00:34:37,090 --> 00:34:38,810
Listen carefully.

404
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:42,280
It doesn't matter who I am,  the important thing

405
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:45,100
is that we need to correct the crime from 20 years ago.

406
00:34:45,100 --> 00:34:48,400
Is that this? Calling the police and avenging?

407
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:51,110
You still don't get it?

408
00:34:51,110 --> 00:34:54,300
There is only one thing Lee Seung Hoon wants.

409
00:34:56,820 --> 00:34:59,000
A sincere apology.

410
00:35:18,900 --> 00:35:20,910
Lee Seung Hoon...

411
00:35:22,570 --> 00:35:24,470
who is he?

412
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:35,060
20 years ago, that guy's father

413
00:35:35,060 --> 00:35:37,300
died at our hospital.

414
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:42,500
The approval for the university hospital was right in front of us,

415
00:35:42,500 --> 00:35:45,130
I didn't want that

416
00:35:45,130 --> 00:35:48,680
death accident to become a lawsuit.

417
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:53,130
Right. If I didn't block that lawsuit by any means possible then,

418
00:35:53,130 --> 00:35:55,520
the hospital would have fallen.

419
00:35:59,150 --> 00:36:02,220
I met that person, Lee Seung Hoon.

420
00:36:04,220 --> 00:36:07,400
I don't want you or that person to become more miserable.

421
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:08,760
Where is he?

422
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,660
Father, apologize to that person.

423
00:36:11,660 --> 00:36:12,760
Apologize?

424
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:16,700
You saw it.  If you sincerely apologize, you can be forgiven.

425
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:18,760
I did nothing wrong.

426
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:23,170
No. I just did my duty for our Myeongwoo.

427
00:36:23,170 --> 00:36:25,440
If you stay like this, something bad might happen to you as well!

428
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,170
Tell him to try.

429
00:36:27,170 --> 00:36:30,910
I, Oh Joon Gyu, won't collapse that easily.

430
00:36:30,910 --> 00:36:32,870
Father.

431
00:36:32,870 --> 00:36:35,000
Leave.

432
00:36:47,230 --> 00:36:48,990
Doctor Park Hoon.

433
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:10,960
I have to be like this so people will believe that it is my surgery. Isn't that so?

434
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:15,000
I heard that General Manager Oh Sang Jin was arrested.

435
00:37:16,070 --> 00:37:18,330
It's Chief Han's work.

436
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:22,260
Who in the world is Chief Han?

437
00:37:22,260 --> 00:37:24,360
Lee Seung Hoon.

438
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:28,820
He's the son of a man who died at Myeongoo because of a medical accident 20 years ago.

439
00:37:30,570 --> 00:37:33,150
I'll take care of that problem.

440
00:37:33,190 --> 00:37:36,540
So don't concern yourself with that and just concentrate on the surgery.

441
00:37:38,220 --> 00:37:42,380
Also,  Park Hoon and his mother,

442
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:47,690
as I promised, I decided to send them to a safe place.

443
00:37:50,100 --> 00:37:52,360
To where?

444
00:38:01,390 --> 00:38:03,330
Are you not feeling well?

445
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:06,530
I came from the prime minister's office.

446
00:38:08,050 --> 00:38:11,780
These are plane tickets to Switzerland and a bit of money for

447
00:38:11,780 --> 00:38:14,430
both you and your mother.

448
00:38:14,430 --> 00:38:15,320
Switzerland?

449
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:20,420
He said once you arrive there, it's your choice to go anywhere you like.

450
00:38:22,230 --> 00:38:23,930
Let's go.

451
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:25,950
I want to meet Jae Hee.

452
00:38:25,950 --> 00:38:29,020
You can not do that. There is no time.

453
00:38:29,020 --> 00:38:33,640
Tell the prime minister that if I don't meet Jae Hee, I'm not going anywhere.

454
00:38:44,660 --> 00:38:47,780
Why do you keep avoiding me? And why aren't you answering the phone?

455
00:38:47,780 --> 00:38:49,340
Take your mother and leave.

456
00:38:49,340 --> 00:38:51,740
I fully understand why you're doing this, but...

457
00:38:51,740 --> 00:38:54,720
No. You can't understand.

458
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:57,400
Your father asked me to save you.

459
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:58,990
He asked me to save you-

460
00:38:58,990 --> 00:39:01,360
That kind of excuse is too cowardly.

461
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,420
I can't  be with you anymore.

462
00:39:03,420 --> 00:39:07,080
So hurry up and leave. That's the best.

463
00:39:07,090 --> 00:39:10,710
I'll take my mother to a safe place and I'll come back for you.

464
00:39:10,710 --> 00:39:12,920
No. Don't come.

465
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:14,880
It's over with you. There's no reason to see you anymore.

466
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:18,410
I promised your father that I would protect you.

467
00:39:18,410 --> 00:39:22,920
If it's because of guilt for making my father die that way, you no longer have to do that.

468
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:26,170
No, it's not because of guilt.

469
00:39:26,170 --> 00:39:29,440
I'll be going. Goodbye.

470
00:39:34,250 --> 00:39:39,310
You can now forget about me and my father's incident.

471
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:43,610
Forget it all and live well.

472
00:40:13,550 --> 00:40:16,020
Tell Prime Minister Jang to come in.

473
00:40:16,020 --> 00:40:16,760
Yes.

474
00:40:17,470 --> 00:40:19,160
What's the problem?

475
00:40:19,160 --> 00:40:20,380
It's probably nothing.

476
00:40:20,380 --> 00:40:24,100
It's more annoying that he's telling me to come and go when it's nothing.

477
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:29,120
Also, tell him to send Park Hoon well so there won't be any further trouble.  Got it?

478
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:31,100
Yes.

479
00:41:29,550 --> 00:41:30,930
What are you doing?

480
00:41:30,930 --> 00:41:33,610
I'm just carrying out my orders.

481
00:41:45,870 --> 00:41:48,990
The surgery is next Monday.

482
00:41:48,990 --> 00:41:51,380
Did you say it was Chief Han Jae Joon?

483
00:41:51,380 --> 00:41:53,140
Yes.

484
00:41:53,140 --> 00:41:57,120
However, about that Doctor Park Hoon...

485
00:41:57,120 --> 00:41:58,670
Yes.

486
00:41:58,670 --> 00:42:01,650
To give up on the surgery... it's very foolish.

487
00:42:01,650 --> 00:42:04,330
It seems that there is no big difference in skills between the two.

488
00:42:04,330 --> 00:42:08,160
I don't understand why he, on his own, threw away

489
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,380
such a good opportunity like this.

490
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:13,370
Just like you said,

491
00:42:13,370 --> 00:42:16,290
he must be foolish.

492
00:42:17,370 --> 00:42:19,900
Foolish....

493
00:42:43,390 --> 00:42:45,120
Yes.

494
00:42:46,060 --> 00:42:47,580
Pardon?

495
00:42:47,580 --> 00:42:49,720
I understand.

496
00:43:02,090 --> 00:43:06,000
He's not foolish, but he probably only thinks about the patient.

497
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:09,530
But the one who won the competition is Chief Han Jae Joon.

498
00:43:09,530 --> 00:43:13,350
Thinking more importantly about a patient's life than winning,

499
00:43:13,350 --> 00:43:16,260
isn't that a doctor?

500
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:18,840
Is that so?

501
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:22,430
If you were a patient,  naturally,

502
00:43:22,430 --> 00:43:26,400
you would choose a doctor like Doctor Park Hoon.

503
00:43:39,490 --> 00:43:41,660
It's me, Doctor Park.

504
00:43:42,590 --> 00:43:47,440
Son of a bit*h!  You had no intention of keeping us alive from the beginning, right?!

505
00:43:47,440 --> 00:43:50,890
You're not dead but still alive, aren't you?

506
00:43:54,180 --> 00:43:59,300
The President chose you as the performing surgeon.

507
00:43:59,300 --> 00:44:03,680
Do you think I'll do as you guys order me to do?!

508
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:05,880
You'll have to.

509
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:08,420
We have your mother.

510
00:44:14,810 --> 00:44:22,990

511
00:44:34,970 --> 00:44:39,290
What do you mean that Park Hoon is performing the surgery?

512
00:44:39,290 --> 00:44:41,090
It's the President's order.

513
00:44:41,090 --> 00:44:44,910
It's his heart, what can I do?

514
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:51,380
Anyway, Park Hoon is still Myeongwoo University Hospital's doctor.

515
00:44:51,380 --> 00:44:54,190
And all the benefits that Myeongwoo Hospital will receive still remain the same.

516
00:44:54,190 --> 00:44:58,130
When the surgery ends, I'll take care of Park Hoon.

517
00:44:58,130 --> 00:45:00,950
So just be patient until then.

